attrs.name: __index
attrs.description: Index of endpoint for owning range

attrs.name: engine_id
attrs.description: ECA engine on Reasoning machine the performed discovery

attrs.name: state
attrs.description: State of access -- completed, in progress, etc

attrs.name: starttime
attrs.description: Date and time this discovery access was created

attrs.name: endtime
attrs.description: Date and time this discovery access ended

attrs.name: is_being_held
attrs.description: True if access is on hold waiting for a scan window

attrs.name: on_hold_duration
attrs.description: How long the access was held waiting for a scan window

attrs.name: _first_marker
attrs.description: True if this is the first DiscoveryAccess for an endpoint

attrs.name: _last_marker
attrs.description: True if this is the last DiscoveryAccess for an endpoint

attrs.name: dark_space
attrs.description: True if when this was the last DiscoveryAccess for an endpoint it was to be treated as dark space

attrs.name: _last_interesting
attrs.description: True if this is the last DiscoveryAccess which accessed an endpoint

attrs.name: discovery_duration
attrs.description: The amount of time taken to establish a session with the endpoint

attrs.name: discovery_duration_sum
attrs.description: The amount of time spent interacting with the endpoint including session establishment

attrs.name: access_failure
attrs.description: True if there are session failures linked to this DiscoveryAccess

attrs.name: access_success
attrs.description: The session type and credential used

attrs.name: _consolidation_done
attrs.description: List of the consolidation appliance identifiers this DA has been be sent to

attrs.name: is_consolidation
attrs.description: If present, always has the value True, and indicates that the data for this DiscoveryAccess originated from a scanning appliance before being consolidated on this one

attrs.name: is_sync
attrs.description: If present, always has the value True, and indicates that the data for this DiscoveryAccess originated from an inferred sync consolidation sender

attrs.name: sync_sender_id
attrs.description: Identifier of inferred sync consolidation sender

attrs.name: sync_sender_name
attrs.description: Name of inferred sync consolidation sender

attrs.name: sync_sender_node_id
attrs.description: Hex node id on inferred sync consolidation sender

attrs.name: no_response_count
attrs.description: The number of no response DAs suppressed onto a single no response DA

attrs.name: last_response
attrs.description: The date of the last response DA

attrs.name: duration
attrs.description: The overall time it took to discover and finish processing the data

attrs.name: inferred_entity
attrs.description: Summary of inferred entity, e.g. Host, NetworkDevice, MFParts

attrs.name: optimized_entity
attrs.description: Summary of skipped entity for this DiscoveryAccess

attrs.name: device_summary
attrs.description: Summary of device information found on DeviceInfo node[device_summary]

attrs.name: slave_pool_used
attrs.description: The Windows Proxy Pool used to obtain device information

attrs.name: slave_used
attrs.description: The Windows Proxy used to obtain device information

attrs.name: credentials_used
attrs.description: The credentials used to obtain device information

attrs.name: is_scanner_file
attrs.description: True if this data came from a scanner file

attrs.name: data_source_summary
attrs.description: Summary of where the data came from

attrs.name: best_ip_score
attrs.description: Best IP score used by endpoint optimisation

attrs.name: scanned_indirectly
attrs.description: Method used to indirectly scan endpoint

attrs.name: provider
attrs.description: Code of cloud or API provider

attrs.name: lpar_minimum_memory

attrs.name: lpar_minimum_virtual_cpus
attrs.description: Minimum number of virtual CPUs this LPAR was defined to ever have

attrs.name: lpar_mode
attrs.description: Indicates whether the LPAR processor capacity is capped, or if it is uncapped and allowed to consume idle cycles from the shared pool. Dedicated LPAR is capped or donating.

attrs.name: lpar_online_memory
attrs.description: The amount of memory currently online (in MB)

attrs.name: lpar_online_virtual_cpus

attrs.description: LPAR group that this LPAR is a member of

attrs.name: lpar_partition_name
attrs.description: Logical partition name as assigned by the HMC

attrs.name: lpar_physical_cpu_percentage
attrs.description: Fractional representation relative to whole physical CPUs that these LPARs virtual CPUs equate to. This is a function of Entitled Capacity / Online CPUs. Dedicated LPARs would have 100% Physical CPU Percentage. A 4-way virtual with Entitled Capacity of 2 processor units would have a 50% physical CPU Percentage.

attrs.name: lpar_shared_physical_cpus_in_system
attrs.description: The number of physical CPUs available for use by shared processor LPARs
attrs.display_name: LPAR Shared Physical CPUs In System

attrs.name: lpar_shared_pool_id
attrs.description: Identifier of Shared Pool of Physical processors that this LPAR is a member

attrs.name: lpar_type
attrs.description: LPAR type: dedicated or shared, SMT enabled or not

attrs.name: lpar_unallocated_capacity
attrs.description: The sum of the number of processor units unallocated from shared LPARs in an LPAR group. This sum does not include the processor units unallocated from a dedicated LPAR, which can also belong to the group. The unallocated processor units can be allocated to any dedicated LPAR (if it is greater than or equal to 1.0) or shared LPAR of the group.

attrs.name: lpar_unallocated_weight
attrs.description: Number of variable processor capacity weight units currently unallocated within the LPAR group

attrs.name: lpar_variable_capacity_weight
